---
const stats = [
  { value: '88%', label: 'of teams using AI coding tools' },
  { value: '6%', label: 'report measurable productivity gains' },
  { value: '45%', label: 'of AI-generated code has OWASP vulns' },
];
---
<section class="pt-32 pb-20">
  <div class="container">
    <!-- Badge -->
    <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-8 fade-up">
      <span class="tag bg-emerald/10 text-emerald border border-emerald/20">
        <span class="inline-block w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-emerald pulse-dot mr-2"></span>
        Agent-Ready SDLC Platform
      </span>
    </div>

    <!-- Headline -->
    <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-extrabold leading-tight max-w-4xl mb-6 fade-up" style="font-family: var(--font-heading);">
      Your AI agents are only as good as your
      <span class="bg-gradient-to-r from-emerald via-blue to-purple bg-clip-text text-transparent">
        engineering infrastructure
      </span>
    </h1>

    <!-- Subtitle -->
    <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-white/50 max-w-2xl mb-10 fade-up">
      Most organizations are adopting AI without changing their underlying infrastructure.
      The result? Agents that hallucinate, pipelines that break, and security gaps that widen.
    </p>

    <!-- CTAs -->
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 mb-16 fade-up">
      <a href="#solutions" class="btn-pill btn-primary">
        Explore Solutions
      </a>
      <a href="https://visdom-ai-maturity-matrix.pages.dev/assessment" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn-pill btn-outline">
        Take the Assessment
      </a>
    </div>

    <!-- Stats strip -->
    <div class="glass-card p-6 md:p-8 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 md:gap-8 fade-up">
      {stats.map(stat => (
        <div class="text-center md:text-left">
          <div class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-1" style="font-family: var(--font-heading);">
            {stat.value}
          </div>
          <div class="text-sm text-white/40">
            {stat.label}
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
